utuwai
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a native plant with a burred seed,  piripiri (bidi-bidi) Acaena sanguisorbae.
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: variant of hutiwai q.v. (also utiwai)
